pokedex_11_01:
Try exploring the Paldea region on foot if you
want to encounter lots of different Pokémon!\c
Remember—Pokémon can be found in tall grass,
caves, oceans, and all sorts of other places!\c
pokedex_11_02:
Battle lots of Trainers to encounter more species
of Pokémon and register them in your Pokédex!\c
Once a Pokémon is registered as “battled,” you
can look up its habitat and find it for yourself!\c
pokedex_11_03:
Trading Pokémon with other Trainers can also
help you fill up your Pokédex!\c
With Surprise Trades, you can trade with players
from all over the world!\c
pokedex_11_04:
Different Pokémon species prefer to be out and
about at different times of day!\c
Try visiting the same place during the morning,
afternoon, evening, and night to encounter a\r
variety of Pokémon!\c
pokedex_11_05:
Are you evolving your Pokémon? There are quite
a few species you can encounter this way!\c
Let your Pokémon battle to gain experience, or
use certain items on them to have them evolve!\c
pokedex_11_06:
There are many Pokémon you can only encounter
through trades!\c
Why not try trading Pokémon with Trainers from
a different academy than your own?\c
pokedex_11_07:
Just a bit more to complete that Pokédex!
You can do it!\c

A-amazing! You completed the Pokédex!\c
That means you’ve encountered every single
Pokémon there is to find in Paldea!\c

in recognition of this magnificent achievement...\c
Come see me in the biology lab back at Naranja
Academy when you have some time!\c
